{"lemma":"جَبْهَةٌ","slug":"جَبْهَةٌ","root":"ج.ب.ه","root_slug":"ج-ب-ه","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ب-ه","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n5019"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D9%87%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"forehead, brow"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"front, face, façade"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"frontline, battlefront"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/d͡ʒab.ha/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n5019","headword_ar":"جَبْهَةٌ","root":"jbh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forehead;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of the face which is the place of prostration:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, Msb, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"even part that is between the eyebrows and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naASiyap","text_ar":"نَاصِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place where the hair grows in the fore part of the head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Kh, JK, Msb, K:) so of a man, (S, Msb,) and of others: (S:) [or,] of a horse, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part that is below the ears and above the eyes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jibaAhN","text_ar":"جِبَاهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljabohapu","text_ar":"الجَبْهَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain Mansion of the Moon; [the Tenth Mansion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K, Kzw;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consisting of four stars;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the four stars"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"text","text":"ζ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"text","text":"γ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"text","text":"η"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and α,] in the neck and heart of Leo;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[regarded by the Arabs as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fore-part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forehead, of Leo;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Kzw in his descr. of Leo;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between each of which and the next to it is the space of a whip's length; the northernmost of them called by astrologers"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^asadu","text_ar":"الاَسَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Kzw in his descr. of the Mansions of the Moon.) ―         -b3-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The moon"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"itself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but [it rather seems to mean the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the disc of the moon; for] it is said in the M that a certain unknown poet has metaphorically assigned a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jbhp","text_ar":"جبهة"},{"kind":"text","text":"to the moon. (TA.) ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jabohapN","text_ar":"جَبْهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chief"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a people, or company of men; (JK, Mgh, K, TA;) like as one says the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajoh","text_ar":"وَجْه"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof. (Mgh, TA.) ―         -b5-  (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generous and manly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manly and noble, persons"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a people, or company of men: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"men exerting themselves in the case of a bloodwit or a debt or other obligation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or in repairing the condition of a poor man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and who come not to any one but he is ashamed to turn them back,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who are seldom or never turned back by anyone:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so, accord. to Aboo-Sa'eed, in a trad. in which it is said that there shall be no poor-rate in the case of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jbhp","text_ar":"جبهة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b6-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A company,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"collected number,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of men, (JK, S, Msb,) and of horses: (JK, Msb:) or, of horses, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"best:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"horses;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, S, M, Mgh, K;) a word having no sing., or n. un.: (M, K:) accord. to Lth, (TA,) having this last meaning in the trad. above mentioned; (S, Mgh, TA;) because horses are the best of beasts. (Mgh.)       -A2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Abjectness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ignominy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, M, K, TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a state of annoyance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"molestation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, TA:) thought by ISd to be from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jabahahu","text_ar":"جَبَهَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ he encountered him with that which he disliked or hated, ” or “ he accused him thereof to his face; ” because the doing this causes one to experience abjectness, or ignominy. (TA.) It is said to have this meaning in a trad., in which it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA_in~a A@ll~`ha qado A^araAHakumo","text_ar":"فَاـِنَّ ا@للّٰهَ قَدْ اَرَاحَكُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Aljabohapi wAls~aj~api wAlbaj~api","text_ar":"مِنَ الجَبْهَةِ والسَّجَّةِ والبَجَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"For God hath relieved you from abjectness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ignominy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and milk diluted with water, and blood drawn"},{"kind":"page_break","n":378},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from a vein"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"], which the Arabs used to eat: or in this trad., (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljabotahapu","text_ar":"الجَبْتَهَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain idol"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that was worshipped in the Time of Ignorance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alsj~p","text_ar":"السجّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albj~p","text_ar":"البجّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"were two idols. (S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sj","text_ar":"سج"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["As","Msb","K","Kh","JK","S","TA","M","Z","ISd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}